  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [x] Foundry\r\n- [x] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\n`forge 0.2.0 (02e430c 2023-07-21T00:24:08.481175000Z)`\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n`forge build`\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS Silicon\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\n#5397 added support for remapping contexts (closing #1855), however, the implementation does not handle all edge cases yet.\r\n\r\nSuppose you have a project structure like this:\r\n\r\n```tree\r\nproject/\r\n└── lib/\r\n    ├── foo/\r\n    │   └── lib/\r\n    │       └── openzeppelin-contracts  \r\n    └── bar/\r\n        └── lib/\r\n            └── openzeppelin-contracts\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn both `foo` and `bar`, `openzeppelin-contracts` is remapped to the following:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n@openzeppelin/contracts/=lib/openzeppelin-contracts/contracts/\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe bug is that only one of the two remappings gets resolved, not both.\r\n\r\n## Error Log\r\n\r\nSneak peek:\r\n\r\n>  Unable to resolve imports: \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC20/IERC20.sol\"\r\n\r\nSee the full log [here](https://app.warp.dev/block/NzkoqBiRAVrpY7IW8d5M0r).\r\n\r\nThe issue is that only the `v2-core` remapping appears in the auto-detected remappings:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nlib/v2-core:@openzeppelin/contracts/=/Users/prb/Sablier/examples/lib/v2-core/lib/openzeppelin-contracts/contracts/\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Clone [sablier-labs/examples](https://github.com/sablier-labs/examples) at commit [eae781](https://github.com/sablier-labs/examples/commit/eae781627e15d963a62c1545fe0944ad94d5519c)\r\n2. Remove the `permit2` remapping in `remappings.txt`\r\n3. Run `forge build`",
